randomNames 0.0-1

We’re pleased to announce the first release of the randomNames package. The package isn’t availabe on CRAN yet so you’ll need to install it off of GitHub.

devtools::install_github("centerforassessment/randomNames")

There’s not much to the randomNames package: Just a single function randomNames.

library(randomNames)
print(randomNames(5))

You can see the documentation for more info on the randomNames arguments.

randomNames is under active development. We :heart: feedback and are happy to answer questions.

randomNames is a Center for Assessment thing.

Developed by Damian W. Betebenner.
